row.entry:
Indicators applied in LCA, PB, SDGs are reviewed to:
- Identify applications and relevant decision contexts;
- Categorize indicators into a DPSIR classification scheme;
- Provide suggestions for indicator systems choice.

Study addressing:
- areas of protection (AoP) to prioritize in LCSA;
- interconnections between AoPs and SDGs.

ce:section.ce:para:
In particular, the following classification was defined to distinguish between different types of approaches that link LCSA and SDGs:

                              •

Type-I: "LCSA-to-SDG", where the main focus is to analyze the SDGs addressed by impact categories used in LC(S)A;


                              •

Type-II: "SDG-based LCSA", where SDGs are used to inform LC(S)A;


                              •

Type-III: "SDG-LCSA mapping", where the main focus is to map SDG and LC(S)A along cause-effect chains;


                              •

Type-IV: "SDG-embedded LCSA", where SDGs is fully integrated in LCSA and its impact pathways.
